output_data.summary: Follow-up for worsening Major Depressive Disorder symptoms, requiring an assessment of suicide risk and titration of Sertraline dosage.
output_data.reasoning: This is a standard psychiatric follow-up addressing recurrence/worsening of Major Depressive Disorder (MDD). The session included assessment of treatment efficacy (Sertraline 50mg), critical suicide risk screening (passive SI), ruling out mania, and subsequent pharmacotherapy adjustment (dose escalation).
